<p><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br>
Frequently asked questions</span><span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"></span><span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"><span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"><br>
</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"><span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"></span></span><span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"><span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);">Q:</span></span><span
 style="color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"></span> How can I upgrade screenie
from an older version to screenie 1.30?<span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"><br>
<span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);">A:</span></span>
dpkg -r screenie &amp;&amp; dpkg -i
screenie_1.30.0-1_all.deb<a href="data/screenie_1.30.0-1_all.deb">
</a><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"></span></p>
<p><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"><span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"><span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);">Q:</span></span><span
 style="color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"></span> </span><span
 style="color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"><span style="color: rgb(51, 0, 51);">How
can I switch
between screen sessions?</span></span><span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"><span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"><br>
<span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);">A:</span></span>
</span><span style="color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"><span
 style="color: rgb(51, 0, 51);">start screenie and choose a&nbsp;
session no. from the menu, to detach
press C-a d (this will return to the screenie interface).</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"></span><span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);">Q: </span>Some
sessions are blocked when I try to choose a session from the menu?
Nothing happened when I choose a session?!<br>
<span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);">A: </span>You
can't select a session which is already attached and in use on another
terminal, detach the related session first.<span
 style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);"><br>
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);">Q:</span><span
 style="font-style: italic;"> </span>Which version of scrennie is
installed on my system?<br>
<span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(255, 102, 102);">A: </span>Type
the follwing command 'screenie -v' <br>
</p>
